    • Method Detail

      • buildInterpreted

        public void buildInterpreted(int occurrenceKey,
                    org.gbif.api.model.occurrence.OccurrencePersistenceStatus status,
                    boolean fromCrawl,
                    @Nullable
                    Integer attemptId,
                    @Nullable
                    UUID datasetKey)
        Builds and persists an Occurrence record by interpreting the fields of the VerbatimOccurrence identified by the passed in occurrenceKey. Note that UNCHANGED occurrences are ignored.
        Parameters:
        occurrenceKey - the key of the VerbatimOccurrence that will be fetched from HBase and interpreted
        status - whether this is a NEW, UPDATED, or UNCHANGED occurrence
        fromCrawl - true if this method is called as part of a crawl
        attemptId - the crawl attempt id, only used for passing along in logs and subsequent messages.
        datasetKey - the dataset that this occurrence belongs to (must not be null if fromCrawl is true)
